  "response": "## The duplicated subtree\n\n`crime_00083` flags the **form footer** — a `<div>` containing a \"Cancel\" `<Link>` back to `/dashboard/invoices` plus a submit `<Button>`. The four occurrences are byte-for-byte identical except for one substring: the submit label is `Create Invoice` in the create forms and `Edit Invoice` in the edit forms.\n\n```jsx\n<div className=\"mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4\">\n  <Link\n    href=\"/dashboard/invoices\"\n    className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n  >\n    Cancel\n  </Link>\n  <Button type=\"submit\">{Create|Edit} Invoice</Button>\n</div>\n```\n\n## Files that change\n\nThe four call sites — replace the footer subtree with `<InvoiceFormActions …/>`:\n\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx` (lines 142–150)\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx` (lines 152–160)\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx` (lines 101–109)\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx` (lines 112–120)\n\nPlus one new file per app (the two trees are isolated workspaces, so the component lives in each):\n\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx` (new)\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx` (new)\n\n## Shared component: `InvoiceFormActions`\n\nThe varying bit is just the submit label, and the cancel destination is conceptually a parameter even though both forms point at `/dashboard/invoices` today. Keep the public API narrow — one required prop, one optional, plus a `children` slot for the rare case where a caller needs to wedge an extra control (e.g., a future \"Delete\" or \"Save draft\" button) without re-forking the layout.\n\n```tsx\ntype InvoiceFormActionsProps = {\n  submitLabel: string;        // \"Create Invoice\" | \"Edit Invoice\"\n  cancelHref?: string;        // defaults to \"/dashboard/invoices\"\n  children?: React.ReactNode; // optional extra controls rendered before submit\n};\n\nexport function InvoiceFormActions({\n  submitLabel,\n  cancelHref = '/dashboard/invoices',\n  children,\n}: InvoiceFormActionsProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4\">\n      <Link\n        href={cancelHref}\n        className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n      >\n        Cancel\n      </Link>\n      {children}\n      <Button type=\"submit\">{submitLabel}</Button>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Public API summary**\n\n| Name | Kind | Required | Default | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `submitLabel` | prop (string) | yes | — | Text on the submit button (the only real difference between create and edit today) |\n| `cancelHref` | prop (string) | no | `/dashboard/invoices` | Lets the component move if the list route ever changes — avoids hard-coding policy |\n| `children` | slot | no | — | Insertion point for extra controls (e.g., delete) without re-duplicating the layout |\n\n**Call-site shape after the refactor**\n\n```tsx\n<InvoiceFormActions submitLabel=\"Create Invoice\" />\n// or\n<InvoiceFormActions submitLabel=\"Edit Invoice\" />\n```\n\n## One caveat worth flagging\n\nThe two trees (`final-example` and `starter-example`) are independent Next.js Learn fixtures, not packages that share code — they each have their own `app/ui/invoices/`. So this is really two parallel extractions, not one. If you want a single source of truth across both, you'd need to first promote a shared workspace package (e.g., `packages/invoices-ui`) — much bigger move than this finding warrants. Per-app extraction is the right scope.",
